cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it addresses the trade-off between standard accuracy and adversarial robustness in models. It also involves analyzing the difference between the sets of features that adversarially robust and standard accurate models depend on, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the vulnerability of models to attacks (cs.CR) and the use of pre-trained models (cs.NE) in low resolution datasets.
